      <scopecontent id="aspace_1d20bf4da40abbd8d4d108d5510255c0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains correspondence between Frank S. Hatch of Longmeadow, MA, and the bookplate designer Frederick Charles Blank of Boston. The collection also contains two Christmas cards and a preliminary pencil sketch by Blank for Hatch's angling bookplate as well as one letter signed by Marian Hatch. In addition to the transactions between artist and patron, the letters also include discussion of bookplate collecting and offers of exchange.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_37faf60ab5d4af6f1401e68c730b91c0">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
